I would submit that non-damaging/healing/buffing abilities are very difficult to balance, since their effects are less tangible and measureable than dmg/healing/buffs, and they are also a lot more open to exploits and creative usage.<br>
<br>
I've seen lots of ideas suggested on many message boards that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> seemed</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> like good ideas to the poster, even many of their readers (myself included at times), which were later shot to pieces when someone pointed out an obvious exploitation of said idea.  It is impossible for the designers to conceive all possible uses.  Further, when you are creating an ability, you have some predetermend notion of how the ability should be used.  It's very easy to evaluate your change in the limited scope of just how <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> you</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> would use it, and not take into account other possible uses.<br>
<br>
